labels.name: Question (JP usage)
labels.description: How to use JP to inspect/modify the AST - please close your question once answered!

issue.body:
Hi,

I'm trying to get the qualified name of the corresponding declaration for a method call expression. I'm using ReflectionTypeSolver() which should resolve classes from the JRE that is currently running (I'm using JavaSE-17). However, it's unable to solve the JShell library :(

When I use ReflectionTypeSolver(false), it is working but is it still checking on the current JRE?

I hope someone can help me here. Thanks!

Here's my code:
`	
	public static void main(String[] args) {
	
	    CompilationUnit cu = StaticJavaParser.parse("public class X {\n" +
	            "        public void test() {\n" +
	            "            try {\n" +
	            "				 List<String> disList = new java.util.ArrayList<>();\n" +
	            "                methodWithExceptions();\n" +
	            "				 jdk.jshell.JShell.create();\n" +
	            "            } catch (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException | ClassCastException e) {\n" +
	            "                System.out.println(e);\n" +
	            "                System.out.println(e.getMessage());\n" +
	            "            }\n" +
	            "        }\n" +
	            "\n" +
	            "        private void methodWithExceptions() throws ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException, ClassCastException {\n" +
	            "            // do something\n" +
	            "        }\n" +
	            "    }");
	    cu.accept(new Visitor(), null);
	}

	private static class Visitor extends VoidVisitorAdapter<Void> {
	    @Override
	    public void visit(MethodCallExpr n, Void arg) {
	        System.out.println("n.toString() = " + n.toString());
	            
			ResolvedMethodDeclaration methodDeclaration = JavaParserFacade.get(new ReflectionTypeSolver()).solve(n)
					.getCorrespondingDeclaration();
			String parentClass = methodDeclaration.declaringType().getQualifiedName();
			System.out.println("***" + parentClass);
	    }
	}
`

issue.title: ObjectCreationExpr typeArgument parsing problem

labels.name: Question (general)
labels.description: Questions not related to using JavaParser

comment.body:
As mentioned in the JLS https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se15/html/jls-15.html
(15.9. Class Instance Creation Expressions)

> UnqualifiedClassInstanceCreationExpression:
new [TypeArguments] ClassOrInterfaceTypeToInstantiate ([ArgumentList]) [ClassBody]

Donc on peut écrire ceci:

> class Foo<T>{}
Foo\<String\> x = new \<String\> Foo();

Here the getTypeArguments() method returns String.
